Re: [PATCH] increase block size limit

Bitcointalk

2010-10-04 19:48:40 UTC - [11]Original Post

   It can be phased in, like:
   if (blocknumber > 115000)
       maxblocksize = largerlimit
   It can start being in versions way ahead, so by the time it reaches
   that block number and goes into effect, the older versions that donʼt
   have it are already obsolete.
   When weʼre near the cutoff block number, I can put an alert to old
   versions to make sure they know they have to upgrade.
